  "id": "019d2e2a-04b6-76d2-b1d0-64943985da35",
  "content": "# Multi-Channel RAG Pipeline — Future Design Note (March 2026)\n\n## Vision\nOne dedicated retrieval channel per memory type, running in parallel, fused via RRF or similar.\n\n## Channel Strategies (Planned)\n- Structural: keyword/exact match (code signatures)\n- Decisional: graph-heavy + vector search\n- Episodic: recency-weighted vector search\n- Analytical: vector search + confidence reranking\n- Procedural: vector search + access-frequency boost\n\n## Compatibility with Tiered Knowledge Design\nThe tiered knowledge feature creates the exact foundation needed:\n- memory_type field = partition key for channel routing\n- Per-type alpha values = per-channel decay behavior\n- Additive composite formula = per-channel weight customization\n- Existing Retriever trait = one implementation per channel\n- MultiChannelRetriever wraps all channels, fuses results\n\n## Implementation Path\n1. Current: single Retriever, filter by memory_type post-search (v1 tiered knowledge)\n2. Future: per-type HNSW indexes for optimal recall\n3. Future: per-type Retriever implementations with specialized strategies\n4. Future: MultiChannelRetriever with configurable FusionStrategy (RRF with k=60)\n\n## No Design Changes Needed\nAll current decisions are forward-compatible. memory_type field is the critical enabler.",
